==English==

===Verb===
'''[[talk]] [[down]]'''
# {{context|idiomatic|lang=en}} To [[negotiate]] a [[lower]] price.
#: ''If he offers a very high price, see if you can '''talk''' him '''down''' before you agree to anything.
# {{context|idiomatic|lang=en}} To [[speak]] [[condescendingly]] or as though the listener is [[inferior]].
#: ''She didn't like how he '''talked down''' to her as though she didn't understand.''
# {{context|flying|lang=en}} To tell an airplane passenger (who has had no flight training) step by step by two-way radio how to land the plane, e.g. if its pilot has become incapacitated while flying.
#: ''The Cessna's pilot had a heart attack while flying, and his non-flying passenger had to be talked down by Air Traffic Control.''

